1. What is the main difference between static and instance methods?
-->👉 Core difference:
    
    Static method
        Belongs to class
        No object required
        Cannot directly access instance data
    Instance method
        Belongs to object
        Object required
        Can access both static & instance data


2. Can a static method call an instance method directly?
-->❌ No
    
    👉 Because:
    
    Static method has no object context
    Instance method needs an object
    
    ✔ But possible using object:
    
    Demo obj = new Demo();
    obj.instanceMethod();



3. Can an instance method call a static method?
-->✅ Yes (directly)

    👉 Because static members are already available
    
    class Demo {
        static void show() {
            System.out.println("Static");
        }
    
        void display() {
            show(); // direct call
        }
    }



4. How does memory allocation differ for static and instance methods?
-->👉 Static Methods
    
    Stored in method area (class area)
    Only one copy
    
    👉 Instance Methods
    
    Associated with objects
    Called via objects stored in heap memory



5. Give a real-world example where you’d use a static vs an instance method.
-->👉 Static method
    
    Utility functions
    Example: Math.sqrt()
    
    👉 Instance method
    
    Object-specific behavior
    Example: student.displayDetails()



Programs
1. Show difference between static and instance methods
-->class Demo {
        static void staticMethod() {
            System.out.println("Static Method");
        }
    
        void instanceMethod() {
            System.out.println("Instance Method");
        }
    
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            Demo.staticMethod(); // no object
    
            Demo obj = new Demo();
            obj.instanceMethod(); // object required
        }
    }



2. Demonstrate calling instance method from static method using object
-->class Demo {
        void show() {
            System.out.println("Instance Method Called");
        }
    
        static void display() {
            Demo obj = new Demo(); // creating object
            obj.show();            // calling instance method
        }
    
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            display();
        }
    }


3. Show that static methods cannot directly access instance variable.
-->class Demo {
        int x = 10;
    
        static void show() {
            // System.out.println(x); ❌ Error
    
            Demo obj = new Demo();
            System.out.println(obj.x); // ✅ correct way
        }
    
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            show();
        }
    }





🔥 Golden Line for Interview

👉 Say this confidently:

"Static methods belong to the class and do not require an object, whereas instance methods belong to objects and can access
  both instance and static members."
